4065 def on_change(self, callback, *args, **kwargs): 

4066 """ 

4067 Register callback function to be called when certain properties or 

4068 subproperties of this object are modified. 

4069 

4070 Callback will be invoked whenever ANY of these properties is 

4071 modified. Furthermore, the callback will only be invoked once even 

4072 if multiple properties are modified during the same restyle / 

4073 relayout / update operation. 

4074 

4075 Parameters 

4076 ---------- 

4077 callback : function 

4078 Function that accepts 1 + len(`args`) parameters. First parameter 

4079 is this object. Second through last parameters are the 

4080 property / subpropery values referenced by args. 

4081 args : list[str|tuple[int|str]] 

4082 List of property references where each reference may be one of: 

4083 

4084 1) A property name string (e.g. 'foo') for direct properties 

4085 2) A property path string (e.g. 'foo[0].bar') for 

4086 subproperties 

4087 3) A property path tuple (e.g. ('foo', 0, 'bar')) for 

4088 subproperties 

4089 

4090 append : bool 

4091 True if callback should be appended to previously registered 

4092 callback on the same properties, False if callback should replace 

4093 previously registered callbacks on the same properties. Defaults 

4094 to False. 

4095 

4096 Examples 

4097 -------- 

4098 

4099 Register callback that prints out the range extents of the xaxis and 

4100 yaxis whenever either either of them changes. 

4101 

4102 >>> import plotly.graph_objects as go 

4103 >>> fig = go.Figure(go.Scatter(x=[1, 2], y=[1, 0])) 

4104 >>> fig.layout.on_change( 

4105 ... lambda obj, xrange, yrange: print("%s-%s" % (xrange, yrange)), 

4106 ... ('xaxis', 'range'), ('yaxis', 'range')) 

4107 

4108 

4109 Returns 

4110 ------- 

4111 None 

4112 """ 

4113 

4114 # Warn if object not descendent of a figure 

4115 # ----------------------------------------- 

4116 if not self.figure: 

4117 class_name = self.__class__.__name__ 

4118 msg = """ 

4119{class_name} object is not a descendant of a Figure. 

4120on_change callbacks are not supported in this case. 

4121""".format( 

4122 class_name=class_name 

4123 ) 

4124 raise ValueError(msg) 

4125 

4126 # Validate args not empty 

4127 # ----------------------- 

4128 if len(args) == 0: 

4129 raise ValueError("At least one change property must be specified") 

4130 

4131 # Validate args 

4132 # ------------- 

4133 invalid_args = [arg for arg in args if arg not in self] 

4134 if invalid_args: 

4135 raise ValueError("Invalid property specification(s): %s" % invalid_args) 

4136 

4137 # Process append option 

4138 # --------------------- 

4139 append = kwargs.get("append", False) 

4140 

4141 # Normalize args to path tuples 

4142 # ----------------------------- 

4143 arg_tuples = tuple([BaseFigure._str_to_dict_path(a) for a in args]) 

4144 

4145 # Initialize callbacks list 

4146 # ------------------------- 

4147 # Initialize an empty callbacks list if there are no previously 

4148 # defined callbacks for this collection of args, or if append is False 

4149 if arg_tuples not in self._change_callbacks or not append: 

4150 self._change_callbacks[arg_tuples] = [] 

4151 

4152 # Register callback 

4153 # ----------------- 

4154 self._change_callbacks[arg_tuples].append(callback)

4156 def to_plotly_json(self): 

4157 """ 

4158 Return plotly JSON representation of object as a Python dict 

4159 

4160 Returns 

4161 ------- 

4162 dict 

4163 """ 

4164 return deepcopy(self._props if self._props is not None else {}) 

4165 

4166 @staticmethod 

4167 def _vals_equal(v1, v2): 

4168 """ 

4169 Recursive equality function that handles nested dicts / tuples / lists 

4170 that contain numpy arrays. 

4171 

4172 v1 

4173 First value to compare 

4174 v2 

4175 Second value to compare 

4176 

4177 Returns 

4178 ------- 

4179 bool 

4180 True if v1 and v2 are equal, False otherwise 

4181 """ 

4182 np = get_module("numpy") 

4183 if np is not None and ( 

4184 isinstance(v1, np.ndarray) or isinstance(v2, np.ndarray) 

4185 ): 

4186 return np.array_equal(v1, v2) 

4187 elif isinstance(v1, (list, tuple)): 

4188 # Handle recursive equality on lists and tuples 

4189 return ( 

4190 isinstance(v2, (list, tuple)) 

4191 and len(v1) == len(v2) 

4192 and all(BasePlotlyType._vals_equal(e1, e2) for e1, e2 in zip(v1, v2)) 

4193 ) 

4194 elif isinstance(v1, dict): 

4195 # Handle recursive equality on dicts 

4196 return ( 

4197 isinstance(v2, dict) 

4198 and set(v1.keys()) == set(v2.keys()) 

4199 and all(BasePlotlyType._vals_equal(v1[k], v2[k]) for k in v1) 

4200 ) 

4201 else: 

4202 return v1 == v2

4254 def __init__(self, plotly_name, **kwargs): 

4255 """ 

4256 Construct a new BaseLayoutType object 

4257 

4258 Parameters 

4259 ---------- 

4260 plotly_name : str 

4261 Name of the object (should always be 'layout') 

4262 kwargs : dict[str, any] 

4263 Properties that were not recognized by the Layout subclass. 

4264 These are subplot identifiers (xaxis2, geo4, etc.) or they are 

4265 invalid properties. 

4266 """ 

4267 # Validate inputs 

4268 # --------------- 

4269 assert plotly_name == "layout" 

4270 

4271 # Call superclass constructor 

4272 # --------------------------- 

4273 super(BaseLayoutHierarchyType, self).__init__(plotly_name) 

4274 

4275 # Initialize _subplotid_props 

4276 # --------------------------- 

4277 # This is a set storing the names of the layout's dynamic subplot 

4278 # properties 

4279 self._subplotid_props = set() 

4280 

4281 # Process kwargs 

4282 # -------------- 

4283 self._process_kwargs(**kwargs) 

4284 

4285 def _process_kwargs(self, **kwargs): 

4286 """ 

4287 Process any extra kwargs that are not predefined as constructor params 

4288 """ 

4289 unknown_kwargs = { 

4290 k: v for k, v in kwargs.items() if not self._subplot_re_match(k) 

4291 } 

4292 super(BaseLayoutHierarchyType, self)._process_kwargs(**unknown_kwargs) 

4293 

4294 subplot_kwargs = {k: v for k, v in kwargs.items() if self._subplot_re_match(k)} 

4295 

4296 for prop, value in subplot_kwargs.items(): 

4297 self._set_subplotid_prop(prop, value) 

4298 

4299 def _set_subplotid_prop(self, prop, value): 

4300 """ 

4301 Set a subplot property on the layout 

4302 

4303 Parameters 

4304 ---------- 

4305 prop : str 

4306 A valid subplot property 

4307 value 

4308 Subplot value 

4309 """ 

4310 # Get regular expression match 

4311 # ---------------------------- 

4312 # Note: we already tested that match exists in the constructor 

4313 match = self._subplot_re_match(prop) 

4314 subplot_prop = match.group(1) 

4315 suffix_digit = int(match.group(2)) 

4316 

4317 # Validate suffix digit 

4318 # --------------------- 

4319 if suffix_digit == 0: 

4320 raise TypeError( 

4321 "Subplot properties may only be suffixed by an " 

4322 "integer >= 1\n" 

4323 "Received {k}".format(k=prop) 

4324 ) 

4325 

4326 # Handle suffix_digit == 1 

4327 # ------------------------ 

4328 # In this case we remove suffix digit (e.g. xaxis1 -> xaxis) 

4329 if suffix_digit == 1: 

4330 prop = subplot_prop 

4331 

4332 # Construct and add validator 

4333 # --------------------------- 

4334 if prop not in self._validators: 

4335 validator_class = self._subplotid_validators[subplot_prop] 

4336 validator = validator_class(plotly_name=prop) 

4337 self._validators[prop] = validator 

4338 

4339 # Import value 

4340 # ------------ 

4341 # Use the standard _set_compound_prop method to 

4342 # validate/coerce/import subplot value. This must be called AFTER 

4343 # the validator instance is added to self._validators above. 

4344 self._set_compound_prop(prop, value) 

4345 self._subplotid_props.add(prop) 

4346 

4347 def _strip_subplot_suffix_of_1(self, prop): 

4348 """ 

4349 Strip the suffix for subplot property names that have a suffix of 1. 

4350 All other properties are returned unchanged 

4351 

4352 e.g. 'xaxis1' -> 'xaxis' 

4353 

4354 Parameters 

4355 ---------- 

4356 prop : str|tuple 

4357 

4358 Returns 

4359 ------- 

4360 str|tuple 

4361 """ 

4362 # Let parent handle non-scalar cases 

4363 # ---------------------------------- 

4364 # e.g. ('xaxis', 'range') or 'xaxis.range' 

4365 prop_tuple = BaseFigure._str_to_dict_path(prop) 

4366 if len(prop_tuple) != 1 or not isinstance(prop_tuple[0], string_types): 

4367 return prop 

4368 else: 

4369 # Unwrap to scalar string 

4370 prop = prop_tuple[0] 

4371 

4372 # Handle subplot suffix digit of 1 

4373 # -------------------------------- 

4374 # Remove digit of 1 from subplot id (e.g.. xaxis1 -> xaxis) 

4375 match = self._subplot_re_match(prop) 

4376 

4377 if match: 

4378 subplot_prop = match.group(1) 

4379 suffix_digit = int(match.group(2)) 

4380 if subplot_prop and suffix_digit == 1: 

4381 prop = subplot_prop 

4382 

4383 return prop 

4384 

4385 def _get_prop_validator(self, prop): 

4386 """ 

4387 Custom _get_prop_validator that handles subplot properties 

4388 """ 

4389 prop = self._strip_subplot_suffix_of_1(prop) 

4390 return super(BaseLayoutHierarchyType, self)._get_prop_validator(prop) 

4391

4393 """ 

4394 Custom __getattr__ that handles dynamic subplot properties 

4395 """ 

4396 prop = self._strip_subplot_suffix_of_1(prop) 

4397 if prop != "_subplotid_props" and prop in self._subplotid_props: 

4398 validator = self._validators[prop] 

4399 return validator.present(self._compound_props[prop]) 

4400 else: 

4401 return super(BaseLayoutHierarchyType, self).__getattribute__(prop) 

4402

4404 """ 

4405 Custom __getitem__ that handles dynamic subplot properties 

4406 """ 

4407 prop = self._strip_subplot_suffix_of_1(prop) 

4408 return super(BaseLayoutHierarchyType, self).__getitem__(prop)

4411 """

4418 """ 

4419 Custom __setitem__ that handles dynamic subplot properties 

4420 """ 

4421 # Convert prop to prop tuple 

4422 # -------------------------- 

4423 prop_tuple = BaseFigure._str_to_dict_path(prop) 

4424 if len(prop_tuple) != 1 or not isinstance(prop_tuple[0], string_types): 

4425 # Let parent handle non-scalar non-string cases 

4426 super(BaseLayoutHierarchyType, self).__setitem__(prop, value) 

4427 return 

4428 else:

4435 if match is None:

4437 super(BaseLayoutHierarchyType, self).__setitem__(prop, value)

4456 def __dir__(self): 

4457 """ 

4458 Custom __dir__ that handles dynamic subplot properties 

4459 """ 

4460 # Include any active subplot values 

4461 if six.PY2: 

4462 

4463 def get_attrs(obj): 

4464 import types 

4465 

4466 if not hasattr(obj, "__dict__"): 

4467 return [] 

4468 if not isinstance(obj.__dict__, (dict, types.DictProxyType)): 

4469 raise TypeError("%s.__dict__ is not a dictionary" "" % obj.__name__) 

4470 return obj.__dict__.keys() 

4471 

4472 def dir2(obj): 

4473 attrs = set() 

4474 if not hasattr(obj, "__bases__"): 

4475 # obj is an instance 

4476 if not hasattr(obj, "__class__"): 

4477 # slots 

4478 return sorted(get_attrs(obj)) 

4479 klass = obj.__class__ 

4480 attrs.update(get_attrs(klass)) 

4481 else: 

4482 # obj is a class 

4483 klass = obj 

4484 

4485 for cls in klass.__bases__: 

4486 attrs.update(get_attrs(cls)) 

4487 attrs.update(dir2(cls)) 

4488 attrs.update(get_attrs(obj)) 

4489 return list(attrs) 

4490 

4491 return dir2(self) + sorted(self._subplotid_props) 

4492 else: 

4493 

4494 return list(super(BaseLayoutHierarchyType, self).__dir__()) + sorted( 

4495 self._subplotid_props 

4496 )
